-- Allied Technologies Drops Most Since May After COO Hedberg Quits
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 2012-01-20T13:27:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/allied-technologies-drops-most-since-may-after-coo-hedberg-quits.html
Allied Technologies Ltd. (ALT) , a maker of
television set-top boxes, headed for its biggest fall in eight
months after saying its chief operating officer quit.  The stock fell as much as 5.3 percent, the most on a
closing basis since May 23, to 52.48 rand and was trading at
52.50 rand as of 3:20 p.m. in Johannesburg.  Chief Operating Officer Jeffrey Hedberg resigned and will
leave the company on a date not yet agreed upon, Johannesburg-
based Altech, as the company is known, said yesterday. Hedberg
joined Altech in July.  To contact the reporter on this story:
